API Health Tracker – File Responsibilities

api-dashboard/
│
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   │    # Marks this folder as a Python package
│
│   ├── main.py
│   │    # FastAPI app entry point
│   │    # Defines API routes:
│   │    #  - /apis → list APIs
│   │    #  - /apis → register API
│   │    #  - /apis/{id}/check → manual health check
│   │    #  - /apis/{id}/history → health check history
│   │    # Handles HTTP requests and dependencies
│
│   ├── database.py
│   │    # Configures the database engine (SQLite)
│   │    # Creates a session factory for DB connections
│   │    # Calls Base.metadata.create_all() to create tables
│
│   ├── models.py
│   │    # Defines database tables as Python classes
│   │    # APIService → stores API info
│   │    # HealthCheck → stores individual health check results
│   │    # Sets relationships (one API → many HealthChecks)
│
│   ├── schemas.py  (future)
│   │    # Optional: Pydantic models for data validation
│   │    # Ensures requests/responses have correct structure
│
│   └── routes/
│        ├── __init__.py
│        │    # Marks routes folder as a package
│        │
│        └── items.py  (future)
│             # Could store API-specific route logic
│             # Allows splitting endpoints into separate files as project grows
│
├── requirements.txt
│     # Lists project dependencies: fastapi, sqlalchemy, requests, uvicorn, etc.
│
├── README.md
│     # Project documentation, usage instructions, and overview
│
└── .gitignore
      # Files/folders Git should ignore (venv, __pycache__, etc.)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

How the Flow Works

1. main.py receives the HTTP request.

2. It calls get_db() from database.py to get a session.

3. Queries or writes happen via models.py.

4. Results are returned as JSON to the client.